le with hair, vertebral defect without open spinal cord, so yes, that's occulta.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.026264,0.049766,0.057894,0.066126,0.074785,0.082888,0.090388,0.095824,0.10395,0.10837,0.11377,0.12997],"unified_progress":[0.03051,0.039353,0.04935,0.058972,0.067428,0.077896,0.083565,0.094605,0.10527,0.11514,0.13036,0.14755]},{"section":31,"text":"The other options like diastematomyelia or tethered cord could be possibilities, but the primary diagnosis here based on the given info is spina bifida occulta.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.022537,0.045426,0.054611,0.062781,0.071446,0.079542,0.087605,0.093411,0.10211,0.10572,0.11626,0.15855],"unified_progress":[0.022636,0.034485,0.043928,0.052759,0.059662,0.070973,0.076667,0.089447,0.10164,0.11213,0.1445,0.19117]},{"section":32,"text":"<answer> Spina Bifida Occulta </answer>","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.026935,0.048809,0.053501,0.059628,0.067847,0.076324,0.084201,0.090778,0.099548,0.10409,0.11624,0.1721],"unified_progress":[0.025731,0.034265,0.040838,0.048436,0.054402,0.065306,0.070229,0.084654,0.097081,0.10957,0.15027,0.21921]}]}}